<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator to Visit Belarus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC),
will visit Belarus between September 5 and 7, the Foreign Ministry
said tonight.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit to Belarus by an NPC Standing Committee
chairman.
</P>
<P>
Li will pay the visit at the invitation of Pavel Shipuk,
speaker of Belarus' House of Republics, and Anatoli Alexandrovich
Malofeyev, speaker of the House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Li is expected to exchange views with
President Alexander Grigorievich Lukashenko and other leading
officials of Belarus on furthering relations between the two
countries and cooperation between their parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Li's visit, which is also a return visit to those by Shipuk and
Malofeyev in 1998, will certainly promote the all-round
development of the friendly exchanges and cooperation between the
two parliaments and the two countries, the Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
