<HEADLINE> Workshop on Conflict Diamonds Held in Namibia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Officials of diamond
producing countries and representatives of various diamond
companies gathered in Windhoek, Namibia on Monday for a two-day
workshop on "conflict diamonds", the Namibian Press Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Namibian Mines and Energy Minister Jesaya Nyamu said the
deliberations were important for countless thousands in Africa
where diamonds had become an aggravating factor in civil conflicts,
such as in Angola and Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
Nyamu said the workshop was also important for those who
depended on the diamond industry for employment, and those who
benefited from public services financed by the substantial tax
revenues generated by the industry.
</P>
<P>
"Clearly the issue of 'conflict diamonds' is a complex one," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
