<HEADLINE> Argentine President Begins Four-Nation Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President
Fernando de la Rua left here Monday for Mexico as part of an 11-
day trip that will also take him to the United States, Canada and
China.
</P>
<P>
In Mexico, he will discuss bilateral issues with his
counterpart Ernesto Zedillo and Mexico's president-elect, Vicente
Fox.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday at noon, he will go to New York to attend the United
Nations Millennium Summit, where he will talk about the role of
the Security Council and meet with U.S. President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by a business delegation, De la Rua will visit
Canada from September 8 to 10 and China from September 10 to 14.
</P>
<P>
In Canada and China, the president will try to attract
investments to Argentina.
</P>
