<HEADLINE> Montreal Apartment Fire Leaves Hundreds Homeless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- An early morning fire engulfed
an apartment complex Monday in Canada's second largest city
Montreal, leaving hundreds of people homeless, according to the
local CTV Newsnet report.
</P>
<P>
As many as 100 firefighters from nearby municipalities rushed
to the scene to help put out the blaze in the four-story building.
</P>
<P>
Several occupants were sent to hospital for injuries caused by
smoke inhalation.
</P>
<P>
Most of the homeless went to their relatives or friends, while
75 others sought help from the local Red Cross.
</P>
<P>
Authorities have not yet known the cause of the fire. 
