<HEADLINE> Lithuania, Ukraine Sign Defense Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania and Ukraine signed an
agreement on cooperation between their defense agencies on Monday,
the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed in Vilnius by Lithuanian Defense
Minister Ceslovas Stankevicius and visiting Ukrainian Defense
Minister Alexander Kuzmuk.
</P>
<P>
