<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 4 (xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates'
(UAE) authorities said that fish caught in the country's waters, as
well as imported fish, were safe and fit for consumption, according
to a report of the official WAM news agency on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In response to reports relating to large amount of dead fish
washed up recently on the coast of Oman, Jassim Mohammed Darwish,
general secretary of the UAE Municipalities, said the UAE was not
affected by the ecological incident which affected Oman or a
similar incident reported recently from Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Millions of dead fish were mysteriously washed up on the coast
of Oman for the second time in the Gulf region during a week, the
UAE's Environment Ministry announced on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
However, the Omani government said no traces of toxicities, oil
spill or any other type of pollution which might have caused the
incident have been found so far. 
