<HEADLINE> British Airways Denies Suspension of Flights to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The British Airways said on
Monday it will not withdraw its services to Harare due to fuel
shortages.
</P>
<P>
As a temporary measure, the British airline said flights from
Harare to London were refueling in Nairobi until sufficient
supplies could be found in Zimbabwe, the Zimbabwe News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The airline's country manager Peter Best denied British media
reports that the airline will suspend services until fuel
shortages in Zimbabwe have subsided.
</P>
<P>
The temporary stops in Nairobi would result in delays of about
two hours to the scheduled service.
</P>
<P>
"Zimbabwe remains a critical and important hub for the British
Airways in east and central Africa," said Best. "Any idea that we
are even contemplating a suspension of the route is rubbish. The
British Airways remains wholly committed behind Zimbabwe."
</P>
<P>
Best said his airline was working with local authorities to
resolve the situation and resume normal non-stop service. 
