<HEADLINE> Collinelli Barred from Italian Olympic Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Olympic pursuit champion Andrea
Collinelli will not be competing in Sydney Olympics after failing
a dope test during the Italian championships in July, Italian
Olympic Committee (CONI) president Gianni Petrucci confirmed on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
"I have not spoken with him, but the situation will not change,
" Petrucci told Italian radio, stating that he was prepared to
sacrifice an Olympic medal for Italy in their battle against
doping.
</P>
<P>
Collinelli, the 1996 Olympic pursuit champion, showed traces of
lidocaine which is used to combat pain and permitted on a
restricted basis, but traces of an anabolic steroid did appear in
the returned test.
</P>
<P>
Collinelli failed to declare he was taking lidocaine before the
race, as the rules indicate.
</P>
<P>
The tests were confirmed and Collinelli was excluded from the
Italian sqaud. 
</P>
</TEXT>
