<HEADLINE> Pakistan Olympic Contingent Leaves for Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Olympic
contingent left for Syndey on Monday with main hopes to win medals
in boxing and field hockey, officials in Karachi said.
</P>
<P>
The batch includes four boxers, two athletes, three rowers and
a shooter.
</P>
<P>
The field hockey team, comprising 16 players and four officials,
was already in New Zealand where it won a four-match series last
week.
