<HEADLINE> Mandela Vows to Help Rebuild Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Former South African
president Nelson Mandela Monday vowed to make war-torn Burundi "a
showpiece of peace and stability", the South African Press
Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Accepting honorary doctorates from two Sydney universities in
Australia, Mandela said he would mobilize international support to
drag the tiny African country out of poverty because poverty has
compounded Burundi's problems.
</P>
<P>
"The roots of the conflict in Burundi run very deep, but the
competition over scarce resources in a poor country adds
significantly to its occurrence and intensity," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is for that reason that I committed myself to mobilizing
international resources and energy to assist in the reconstruction
and development of the Burundi economy," he added.
</P>
<P>
Mandela helped broker a peace accord last month aimed at ending
the seven-year-old civil war in Burundi which has cost more than
200,000 lives. However, there are still many problems yet to be
resolved before the country can achieve full peace. 
