<HEADLINE> Kusatsu Launches Motor Production Venture in Zhuhai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Kusatsu Electric Co., Ltd. of
Japan today started a business in the city of Zhuhai in south
China's Guangdong Province to produce motors for home appliances
with an investment of 12 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the manufacturing venture will be
situated inside Qingwan Industrial Zone of Zhuhai, one of China's
four earliest special economic zones.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese-backed business will finish construction,
including installation of automated production lines, and begin
production in next February. By then, it will have a capacity to
produce 1.8 million sets of motors of different kinds, with the
annual output value amounting to 200 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Party and government authorities of Zhuhai urged concerned
local departments to go all out to serve overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Kusatsu first entered China by starting up a company in
Shanghai in 1993. 
</P>
