<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market on Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Most funds on the securities
investment fund market dropped under the impact of quick declines
on the stock market today.
</P>
<P>
According to the NAVs report released today, all funds were on
the decline last week.
</P>
<P>
However, the drops were on average smaller than those of the
composite indices on the stock market, according to Homeway, China
's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Restructured funds such as Fund Tongzhi, Fund Jinding and Fund
Xingke were the top losers today, dropping 4.64 percent, 3.01
percent and 2.94 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Among the 30 funds on the fund market, only Fund Kaiyuan went
upwards today. Another eight funds remained unchanged as the rest
declined.  
</P>
