<HEADLINE> State Councilor on Preparations for Census </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- State Councilor Wang Zhongyu
has urged local governments to attach great importance to
preparations for the forthcoming fifth national census, due to
start on November 1.
</P>
<P>
Wang, also head of a State Council leading group on the census,
was speaking at today's conference attended by heads of provincial
leading groups on the issue from all provinces, municipalities and
ethnic autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
The fifth national census is aimed at making clear of the
population's total number, quality, structure and distribution,
which is of great importance for working out the country's 10th "
five-year plan" (2001-2005) and its economic and social
development in the 21st century, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He criticized some local officials for their wrong views of
various issues. On behalf of the State Council, Wang reiterated
that the fifth census is a major government work for this year and
must not fail.
</P>
<P>
The concerned policies and regulations must be carried out
precisely, so as to acquire accurate information on the population,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that no illegal charges are allowed during the
population surveying and that the information collected during
this census must not be used to punish anyone for their past
mistakes on population-related matters.
</P>
<P>
Terming the fifth census as the world's largest of its kind,
the state councilor demanded a strong task force be organized to
ensure that the census goes smoothly. All work units should be
mobilized to take part in the census, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
