<HEADLINE> Central Socialism Academy Starts New Term </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The multi-party cooperation
system led by the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the political
consultation system conform with China's situation and has
enormous advantages, a senior official said today.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoguo, a vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and head of the United Front
Department of the CPC Central Committee, made the remark at a
ceremony to mark the opening of the autumn term of the Central
Socialism Academy.
</P>
<P>
Under the systems, he said, different non-communist parties are
uniting and cooperating with the CPC in a joint effort to build
socialism.
</P>
<P>
As participating partners, these non-communist parties hold
political consultations with the CPC on major issues, so as to
materialize scientific and democratic decision-making while
supervising the ruling party, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The non-communist parties are existing as close friends and
partners of the CPC rather than opposition parties, Wang said. He
called it as a strategic task to train young and middle-aged
cadres of these non-communist parties and build up a high-quality
teams of cadres for the parties.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the CPPCC National Committee, the academy was
founded in 1956. It was forced to suspend when the "Cultural
Revolution" broke out in 1966 and was reopened in 1983.
</P>
<P>
The academy is a united party school of democratic and non-
party personages, and a college for the advanced training of
cadres of non-communist parties and other prominent figures
outside the Communist Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
