<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Surge 2.3 Percent on Eased Interest Rate Fears </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks prices
registered across-the-board gains on Monday as further U.S.
interest rate hikes this year eased.
</P>
<P>
The market was driven up by property and banking shares after
benign U.S. data boost optimism that near term interest rates in
the U.S. may have peaked, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index surged 392.56 points, or 2.26
percent, to close at 17,726.17, after ending the morning session
with a 1.75 percent gain.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 11.091 billion HK dollars (1.422 billion U.S.
dollars), compared to Friday's 9.828 billion HK dollars (1.260
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
All the four Hang Seng sub-index heaped heavy gains, among
which properties made the best performance with a rise of 535.57
points, or 2.80 percent.
</P>
<P>
The sub-index of Finance, Utilities and Commerce &AMP; Industry
advanced by 1.76 percent, 0.86 percent and 2.25 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index rose 1.24 percent to 526.
33 while the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp Index grew by 2.22
percent to 1,399.90.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index went up 2.65 percent to 2,838.27 and
Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index rose 1.81 percent to 3,429.36.
</P>
</TEXT>
