<HEADLINE> U.S. to Begin Training Nigerian Army in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 4 (Xinhua) -- U.S. military experts will begin
to train five battalions of Nigerian soldiers in October this year
to bolster Nigeria's peacekeeping capability, Nigerian press
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
This goes with a 42 million U.S. dollars training program
finalized during U.S. President Bill Clinton's recent visit to
Nigeria, U.S. embassy officials in the West African country were
quoted as saying during the weekend.
</P>
<P>
