conducted by 300 U.S. special forces, would involve Nigerian
military units based in such cities as Enugu, Ibadan, Kano, Lagos
and Sokoto.
</P>
<P>
The training will focus mainly on combat, life saving, U.S.
training methodology, human rights, rules of engagement and other
related issues so as to invest the Nigerian troops with "robust"
peacekeeping capability and "increased ability to coordinate
complex operation", they said. 
