<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills 14 in NW China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people were killed
and seven others were injured in a bus accident which occurred on
Sunday morning in Guyuan County, in northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The double-decker bus was moving from Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region, northwest China, to Henan Province, central China. It
slammed into a cliff at 7:40 am after crashing into a truck
because of fast speed and a dense fog.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen of the 42 passengers aboard the bus were killed
instantly, and one died on the way to a local hospital. All the
injured passengers were sent to local hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Further investigation into the case is continuing.  
</P>
