<HEADLINE> Suspected Police Murderer Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A suspected murderer who shot
dead two policemen was arrested Monday night in neighboring Hebei
Province, a spokesman for the Beijing Public Security Bureau said
today.
</P>
<P>
Han Xuegong, 33, a former bank employee in Botou City of Hebei
Province, was found gambling in Fengtai District, southwestern
Beijing, on the evening of September 1 by patrolling police.
</P>
<P>
Han shot at the policemen when they were questioning him.
Policemen Ma Fuliang, 27, and Zhou Wenli, 21, were killed, while
Policeman Zhao Jingshan, 20, was wounded.
</P>
<P>
During the investigation, the police discovered that Han had
been suspected of stealing guns. Han and his girlfriend Xu
Zhenzhen, the suspected accomplice, were arrested in Shijiazhuang,
capital city of Hebei Province last night.
</P>
<P>
The police seized Han's gun in Fangshan District, in Beijing's
southwestern outskirts, in the wee hours this morning.
</P>
<P>
The case is under further investigation.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources, more than 5,000 police died on
duty during the last two decades, with another 100,000 wounded.
</P>
<P>
In 1999 alone, 533 policemen died and 5,885 were wounded on
duty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
