<HEADLINE> Trade Fair to Promote China's Investment in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 4 (Xinhua) -- An investment and trade fair
promoting economic exchange and cooperation between African
countries and China's Hubei province was hosted today in Wuhan,
the provincial capital of Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The fair will help economic organizations and enterprises in
Hubei learn more about Africa, said Hubei provincial governor
Jiang Zhuping.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiang, the province is to import more African
commodities and improve cooperation with African countries in the
fields of agricultural technology, farming machinery, biological
techniques and telecommunication.
</P>
<P>
Local steel and automobile manufacturers have set up plants and
businesses in African countries, the governor said.
</P>
<P>
Embassy and diplomatic officials from a dozen of African
countries including Egypt, Cameroon, Nigeria and Mozambique
attended the fair.
</P>
<P>
They said investment from China is welcomed in African
countries.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the bilateral trade value between China and Africa
was recorded at 6.48 billion U.S. dollars. Chinese enterprises set
up 351 investment projects in the African continent and signed
nearly 10,000 cooperation contracts valued at more than 14 billion
U.S. dollars.  
