<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Separate Blasts Kill 2, Injure 11 in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Two persons died while 11
others were injured in two incidents triggered by grenade blasts
Sunday in Cotabato province in the southern Philippines, the
official Philippines News Agency said Monday in a report.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the first explosion occurred in a
benefit dance in Libungan town after a drunkard dropped a hand
grenade in the middle of the dance floor that killed him and
another male. Nine people were hurt in the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in Pigcawayan town, two farmers were injured when an
M-79 grenade landed at their farm lot in a remote village.
</P>
<P>
Investigators are still trying to determine the perpetrators'
motive in both incidents.
</P>
<P>
Only last Thursday, three separate blasts rocked Kidapawan City
and Kabacan town, both in Cotabato province. A total of 19
civilians were injured, including an 11-year-old boy who is
suffering from third degree burns.
</P>
<P>
Authorities are not discounting the possible involvement of the
secessionist Moro Islamic Liberation Front rebels in the blasts.
</P>
</TEXT>
