<HEADLINE> 18 Killed, 15 Missing in Road Accident in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A speeding bus carrying 55
passengers fell into a gully between Shekhupura and Lahore of
Punjab Province late Sunday night, killing 18 people while the 15
missing are also feared dead, police said.
</P>
<P>
According to details, police have so far recovered 18 bodies
from the site of the incident as the rescue and search operations
continued Monday morning. Those who were killed include a woman
and a child. Twenty two others who sustained injuries were
admitted to hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Efforts are underway by army divers and the local
administration to search for the remaining 15 persons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
