<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed broadly lower Monday in thin
trading.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 23.50
points to 743.52, the all-share Emas Index slipped 5.32 points to
186.79, the Industrial Index dipped 27.08 points to 1,372.06, the
Technology Index fell 6.35 points to 96.27 and the Second Board
Index shed 4.40 points to 195.17.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 662 to 68 while 58 counters were
unchanged and 211 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover decreased to 104.444 million shares valued
at 413.925 million ringgit (108.92 million U.S. dollars) from 132.
661 million shares worth 579.65 million ringgit (152.53 million U.
S. dollars) last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
