<HEADLINE> S.Korean Machine Export to Southeast Asia Up 20 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 4 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's machine exports to
Southeast Asian nations rose 20 percent in July from last year to
11.6 billion U.S. dollars, the Korea Trade-Investment Promotion
Agency said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The rise came from boosted exports of semiconductor
manufacturing equipment, machine tools and fabric processing
appliances due to economic recovery and the establishment of
industrial infrastructures in the southeast Asian region.
</P>
<P>
Singapore, Malaysia, Vietnam and Thailand all increased imports
by more than 20 percent in the first half of the year from the
same period last year, said the agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
