<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-Share Market Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-Share Index
rebounded 2.88 points, or 2.43 percent to close at 121.16 points
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover was 99.43 million HK dollars, 1.5 percent less
than last Friday's total, according to Homeway, China's leading on-
line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market managed to rally from the recent tumble during a
volatile trading session Monday, closing slightly off its intraday
high of 121.35 points.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers by 46 to nine, with one unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Tsann Kuen rose 7.74 percent to 3.34 HK dollars per share,
while Orient Elect rallied 7.03 percent to 3.96 HK dollars per
share.
</P>
<P>
Konka Elec fell 4.36 percent to 5.05 HK dollars per share,
while Jiangling Moto dipped 2.91 percent to 1.67 HK dollars per
share.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the rally was due to correction of the market.
They predict that the market is to remain volatile despite an
overall positive trend in the next session.  
</P>
