<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-Share Market Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
closed at 616.54 points on Monday, up 5.15 points or 0.84 percent
compared with last week's close. The sub-index closed at 4,818.69
points, down 35.76 points or 0.75 percent.
</P>
<P>
Turnover totaled 9.6 billion yuan, 6.8 percent less than last
Friday's 10.3 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Composite Index opened one point lower than last
close at 610.39 points before touching a low of 606.66 points in
the afternoon. Then the index rebounded as big buyers cashed in.
</P>
<P>
However, turnover was low due to caution of investors despite
the news about the China Securities Regulatory Commission's five
measures to improve the stock market. The measures are believed to
boost investor confidence.
</P>
<P>
Tonghua Goldhorse Medicine Co., Ltd. was the top gainer with
its price growing ten percent to the ceiling of 21.95 yuan per
share.
</P>
<P>
Donguan Winnerway Industrial Zone Ltd. was the biggest loser,
with its price plummeting 5.24 percent to 7.6 yuan per share
amidst profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that the A-share market is to continue the
rally well into the week. However, the 625-point level may be a
test Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
