<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-Share Market up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share Index
rallied 4.11 points or 6.38 percent to its intraday high of 68.59
points Monday, posting its biggest gains since Aug. 21st
</P>
<P>
Turnover shrank to 20.54 million U.S. dollars, which was 37.91
percent less than Friday's total, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Following a week's tumble, selling pressure gradually eased off.
As evidenced, trade volume continued to contract, as investors
were no longer much convinced of a bearish trend.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, buying interest seemed to have resurfaced on
speculation that China may soon relax its restriction of issues of
different classes of shares to allow B-share or H-share companies
to gain access to the A-share market.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predict that the market has seen signs of life
with the underlying tone improving as it is convinced that China
markets will witness upward moves in the long run. 
</P>
