<HEADLINE> China's T-bond Market Sluggish on Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond market turned
inactive as several new share issues and stock placements
tightened the money supply on the market. A bond was posted at one-
day suspension, and the transaction value of the other bonds
totaled only 944 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Three current treasuries on the market edged up with gains
ranging from 0.02 percent to 0.10 percent while another two lost
by 0.14 percent on average. Trade on Bond 009704 was suspended
Monday for interest payment, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The new floating-rate 010004, whose coupon rate is 2.87 percent
this year, rose by 0.10 percent to 104.60 yuan, recouped some
losses of last Friday. The yield of the bond was stable at 2.39
percent.
</P>
<P>
000696 closed the session down 0.18 percent to 143.92 yuan,
pushing the yield up 0.05 percentage points to 3.75 percent. The
trade on the bond was sluggish with a turnover of 61 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
China's repo transactions boomed with a broad rise in the
repurchasing prices, fueled by the speedup of stock public sales.
Trade volume of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day
repurchasing transactions totaled 13.78 billion yuan, up 171.27
percent from last Friday. The interest rate of the three-day
repurchasing agreement leapt to 3.5 percent from 0.89 percent on
the previous close. 
</P>
</TEXT>
