<HEADLINE> Asian Political Parties Conference to Open in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The first International
Conference of Asian Political Parties will be held here this month
to discuss political, economic and socio-cultural cooperation in
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The conference, scheduled for September 17-20, is aimed at
bringing about cooperation among political parties of Asia in the
first years of the new millennium, Jose De Venecia, Vice President
of the Christian Democrat and People's Parties International of
the Philippines, said at a press briefing here Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Our purpose is to see how the political parties can now draft
a strategy for political and economic strategy in Asia in the
first 25 years of the 21st century," said De Venecia, Chairman of
the organization committee of the conference.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one Asian countries, including China, Japan, South Korea
and India, will send official delegates to the conference,
according to him, who is also the former Speaker of the House of
Representatives.
</P>
<P>
In addition, political parties from the United States,
Australia and eight other countries from Africa, South America and
Western Europe will attend the conference as observers and special
guests.
</P>
<P>
De Venecia said the conference will issue a joint declaration,
Asian Declaration 2000, which will touch on major policy issues
ranging from economic development to security and peace in Asia.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the conference, the first of
its kind being held in Asia, can be established as an event in
Asia once every two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
