<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket
ended higher Monday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark S&AMP;P/ASX 200 added 5.8 points to 3337.5, while all
ordinaries ended six points higher at 3299.4.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 437 million shares worth 1.26 billion
Australian dollars (726.52 million U.S. dollars). Falling stocks
outnumbered rises, 817 to 649, with 505 stocks remaining steady.
</P>
<P>
Gains in News Corp provided the main momentum for the market.
Its ordinary shares jumped 1.187 Australian dollar to 24.345
Australian dollars, while its preferred scrip rose 1.074
Australian dollars to 21.064 Australian dollars. Publishing and
Broadcasting lost 27 cents to 14.30 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Banking stocks were mixed. The Commonwealth shed 73 cents to 27.
17 Australian dollars. Westpac eased 3.9 cents to 12.751
Australian dollars and ANZ added nine cents to 13.08 Australian
dollars. NAB lifted 4.9 cents to 25.848 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Telstra shares fell four cents to 6.40 Australian dollars.
Cable &AMP; Wireless Optus eased four cents to 4.60 Australian dollars
and AAPT was steady at 7.10 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the resource sector, BHP added 20.6 cents to 19.246
Australian dollars and Rio Tinto lifted 24 cents to 26.54
Australian dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
