<HEADLINE> Share prices Move Lower in Tokyo for Fifth Straight Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed lower in
Tokyo for the fifth straight trading day Monday on selling stirred
following gains in early trading.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 51.57 points, or 0.31
percent from last Friday's close to end at 16,688.21.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 5.08 points or 0.34 percent to 1,502.
40.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 500.49 million
shares from last Friday's 639.95 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi Cable Industries was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented high-tech issues were generally down, hit by
the strong yen, while losers included retailers, the rubber, drug
and brokerage sectors.
</P>
<P>
Information and telecom issues were mixed, while the mining,
oil and real estate sectors drew active buying.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 721 to 535, while 161 issues closed unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
