<HEADLINE> China to Produce Universal Blood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- China will begin to
manufacture universal blood with the help of a new technology that
turns blood of different types into a universal one via transgenic
engineering, according to sources.
</P>
<P>
The technology has been developed by the Institution of
Transfusion under the Chinese Academy of Military Medicine, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Huayu Group and the Tianjin New Technology Industrial Park
will jointly set up the Huayu Bio-Garden Development Co. Ltd., to
manufacture the blood, with an investment of 240 million yuan (
about 29.3 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new company will be located in the Torch Venture Garden of
the industrial park in north China's port city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
According to some experts involved in the research, so far,
they have succeeded in transforming the "B" type of blood to the "
O" type.
</P>
<P>
They said that the transformations from the "A" group to the "O
" group and from porcine blood to human's are being studied and
are expected to be put into future industrial production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
