<HEADLINE> Arabs Support Palestinian Efforts to Recover East Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Arab countries have expressed
unanimous support to the Palestinian people for all their struggles
to restore sovereignty over East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Arab foreign ministers opened the 114th session of the Arab
League council on Sunday to discuss the Palestinian-Israeli peace
negotiations, especially the issue of Jerusalem. The ministers
released a statement late Sunday night reiterating rejection of any
attempts aimed at tampering with Palestinian sovereignty over the
holy city.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli negotiations have been stuck over the
issue of Jerusalem, which both sides claim as their capital.
</P>
<P>
Arab countries support all efforts exerted by the Palestinian
people to restore self-determination and freedom, and the
declaration of an independent Palestinian state with Jerusalem as
the capital within this year, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It called on the international community to recognize the
Palestinian state when it is declared.
</P>
<P>
It urged Israel to withdraw from the occupied Arab territories,
including East Jerusalem, to the borders of June 4, 1967 under the
United Nations Security Council resolutions 242 and 338.
</P>
<P>
The Arab countries stressed that Palestinian refugees have the
right to return and Israel must shoulder legal, political and moral
responsibilities for the refugee problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
