<HEADLINE> Manila Stocks End Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Manila stocks closed slightly
higher Monday as investors continued to position in heavily-
battered blue chip issues.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, rose 2.99
points to close at 1,532.64.
</P>
<P>
But the broader all-shares index shed 8.03 points to 698.62.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 183.3 million shares worth some 11.9 million
U.S. dollars on Monday against last Friday's 562.9 million shares
worth some 20.3 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the market's up-tick was tempered by the
continued weakening of the local currency.
</P>
<P>
"There have been some bargain hunting, but the continued
weakness of the peso affected the market," said Jonas Ravela, an
analyst at Equitable PCIBank Securities.
</P>
<P>
The peso averaged 45.218 pesos against the U.S. dollar early
Monday, weaker compared to last Friday's close of 45.15 pesos.
</P>
<P>
Most of the market's major subsectors ended higher, except for
the property sector which fell 8 points to 490.72.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers, 34 to 21, while 39 issues were
unchanged. 
</P>
