<HEADLINE> Depression Maring Leaves 2 Dead in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- At least two persons were
killed as many parts of Metro Manila were flooded Monday by
continuous rain brought by tropical depression Maring, the
Philippine National Disaster Coordinating Council said.
</P>
<P>
The council said in a report that one of the victims was 59-
year-old Froilan Elada, who died of heart attack. The other victim,
the 33-year-old Feliciano Pancho, died from drowning and remained
missing.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, 1,129 families in Metro Manila have
evacuated to higher grounds and classes in all levels were
suspended in the city.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of commuters stranded and scores of vehicles stalled
by the floods as a result of the heavy rain which lashed Metro
Manila continuously for six hours beginning at midnight.
</P>
<P>
The government has dispatched 11 military trucks and some boats
to help the affected residents.
</P>
<P>
The weather authorities said Maring will continue to bring
rains over Luzon, including Metro Manila in the near future.
</P>
</TEXT>
