<HEADLINE> Health Most Important to Chinese in Cyber Age </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and other people of
the Asia-Pacific rate health as the most important thing in their
life, according to the latest survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey done by MasterCard on the consuming trends among
Asians showed that 45 percent of the Asian people polled rated "
health" as the most important aspect to their life.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-one percent of the Chinese surveyed put "health" atop
their list. One in five Chinese chose "family and friends" as the
second most important.
</P>
<P>
"Making money" ranked fifth on the list following "work" and "
happiness". Only four percent believed that making money was the
most essential thing to them.
</P>
<P>
Feng Weiquan, senior vice president of MasterCard, said that
the result indicated that Chinese are still keeping their
traditional virtues as they care about health, family and
happiness in an age when cyber millionaires occur overnight.
</P>
<P>
The survey was done among 5,447 people from 13 countries and
regions in the Asian-Pacific region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
