<HEADLINE> Longtan Hydropower Plant in Pre-Construction Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Preparations for construction
of a new hydropower station on the Hongshui River in south China
have been carried out as planned.
</P>
<P>
Longtan hydropower station, which will be situated in Tian'e
County, Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, will have a generating
capacity of 5.4 million kw. It has been listed by the state as
one of the major projects aimed at speeding up development in west
China.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Li Zhinong, deputy manager of
Longtan Hydroelectric Development Co. Ltd., said that 530 million
yuan (one U.S. dollar equals 8.3 yuan) would be raised this year
to finance the pre-stage construction.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory construction included building two highways
with a combined length of 95 km connecting the construction site
to the outside world, transport facilities, water and power supply
works inside the construction site, as well as facilities to store
construction materials.
</P>
<P>
By late July, 199 million yuan of the funds required had been
paid and 133 million yuan had been spent on construction.
</P>
<P>
Building of the two highways has already finished.
</P>
<P>
Li said that other jobs also needed completing including,
relocating residents from the reservoir area, acquiring land,
raising funds, in addition to constructing facilities for
transport, water and power supply inside the construction site, as
well as works to store construction materials in the second half
of the year.
</P>
<P>
Longtan hydropower station is one of several key power plants
that are planned to be built to utilize hydroelectric resources on
the Hongshui River. Planning and prospecting of the project began
in 1958. 
</P>
</TEXT>
