<HEADLINE> Tibetan Children's Art Troupe Performs in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 3 (Xinhua) - A Tibetan Children's Art
Troupe staged successfully its first performance today in Santiago,
capital of Chile.
</P>
<P>
The young artists' splendid show, which took place in the Andes
Cultural Center, received a warm response and the packed theater
was imbued with laugh and applause.
</P>
<P>
Among the audience were General Comptroller of the central
government Arturo Aylwin, Chief of the Andes Cultural Center
