<HEADLINE> 3 Drowned in Boat Accident in Maluku, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- At least three passengers were
drowned in a boat accident in waters off Maluku islands, Indonesia,
according to The Jakarta Post Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Mulya Star, a boat carrying 43 people, sank off the Manipa
strait near Ambon, capital of Maluku Province, on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
As of Sunday night, a total of 24 people have been rescued and
three others were found dead by navy rescue teams.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue the search effort while identification of the
victims is under way," Eastern Fleet security chief Commodore
Djoko Sumaryono said.
</P>
<P>
The navy has also deployed a Nomad airplane to help in the
efforts.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the boat was hit by strong winds and a
huge tidal wave when entering the Manipa strait, causing the
vessel to sink.
</P>
<P>
"Everything was normal but suddenly we were hit by a strong
surge on the left side of the boat ... I saw people trying to swim
and hold on to things," said Irwan, an engine crew member who
survived the ordeal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
