<HEADLINE> Cacho Pulls Out Spanish Olympic Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Spain's former Olympic 1,500
metees champion Fermin Cacho pulled out of the Spanish Olympic
team for the Sydney Games on Sunday because of injury.
</P>
<P>
Cacho, gold medalist in 1992 and silver medalist in 1996, has
been struggling with an Achilles tendon injury and completed his
first 1,500m race of the season in the semi-finals of the Spanish
championships in Barcelona on Saturday. He was due to compete in
the final later on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But as Cacho found that he was not in good shape to compete in
Sydney, he announced on Sunday his decision to pull out of the
Games.
</P>
<P>
Jose Antonio Redolat is likely to replace Cacho in the Spanish
squad, joining Andres Diaz and Reyes Estevez in the 1,500 metees
event. 
