ninth stage and took the overall lead in the Tour of Spain cycling
race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The ONCE rider negotiated the technical route of 36.7
kilometers in Tarragona, Spain, averaging just over 50 kph.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Alex Zuelle finished more than two minutes behind
Olano and had to surrender the race leader's gold jersey to the
Spanish rider.
</P>
<P>
Another ONCE rider Santos Gonzalez finished second in the stage
in a time 13 seconds slower than that of Olano and Gonzalex was
fifth in the overall standings.
</P>
<P>
World time-trial champion Jan Ullrich of Germany conceded over
a minute to Olano, taking sixth place overall, partly due to a
puncture after 15 km. 
