<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portugal Beats Estonia in World Cup Soccer Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Portugal beats Estonia 3-1 in
its first match of the European Qualifier for the 2002 World Cup
Finals in Talin, Estonia, on Sunday, according to Portuguese
national TV.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese midfielder Rui Costa opened the score with a long
drive at 15th minute. His teammate Luis Figo added a goal with a
direct free kick at the 49th.
</P>
<P>
Seven minutes later, Sa Pinto made it 3-0 for his team with a
header when he converted a lobbing pass by Figo.
</P>
<P>
Portugal will meet Ireland on October 7 in Group 2 which also
includes the Netherlands, Cyprus and Andorra. 
</P>
</TEXT>
