<HEADLINE> Castro Supports Belarus-Russia Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro
supports the future union of Russia and Belarus, visiting
Belarusian leader Alexander Lukashenko said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko said at a press conference that this eventual union
has been talked over with President Castro, who expressed his
support.
</P>
<P>
The Belarusian leader ratified the will of his government to
achieve this new federation and reminded that both nations have
already signed three agreements, as a basis to the unification.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko said that between Moscow and Minsk, everything has
been agreed upon regarding commercial and economic relations, and
that there is already a common customs system space.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the free movement of both countries' citizens
around their common territory is a fact, as well as the
constitution of a common military command to defend the borders of
both states.
</P>
<P>
Soon there will be an advance in the unification of taxation
laws and in the elaboration of a common currency, said the
Belarusian President, who arrived at Havana last Saturday, as part
of what is the first visit of a Belarusian leader to Latin America.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Lukashenko and Cuban President Fidel Castro
signed a friendship and cooperation treaty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
