<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A period of intense telephonic
briefing between the diplomatic chiefs of the leading powers
continued Monday with talks between Italian Foreign Minister
Lamberto Dini and U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright.
</P>
<P>
the Italian news agency Ansa said that their conversation
concentrated primarily on various aspects of the Balkans crisis
and the Israeli-Palestinian peace talks.
</P>
