<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives for U.N. Millennium Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived in New York Monday evening to attend the Millennium Summit
to be held at the United Nations headquarters on September 6-8.
</P>
<P>
More than 150 heads of state or government from around the
world will participate in the summit meeting, the largest-ever in
the U.N. history, to discuss the challenges the world faces and
the actions to be taken in the new century.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang will deliver a speech on China's stand on major
issues at a plenary session and take part in a U.N. Security
Council summit and one of the four roundtable discussions. He will
also meet with the leaders of some countries during the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
